    description: `Private Devotions for Morning and Evening is a carefully compiled pocket-sized book that gathers the essential supplications and remembrances prescribed by Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) for the beginning and end of each day. Drawing upon authentic hadith sources, this compact volume presents the morning adhkar (azkar al-sabah) and the evening adhkar (azkar al-masa') that form a protective spiritual routine for every believing Muslim. The book begins with the morning supplications, including the well-known du'as that the Prophet recited upon waking, such as "Alhamdulillahilladhi ahyana ba'da ma amatana wa ilayhin-nushur" (All praise is for Allah who gave us life after death and to Him is the return), and the ayat al-kursi which the Prophet described as the greatest verse in the Quran and a guarantee of protection when recited in the morning. The evening section mirrors this structure with the corresponding adhkar recommended after the Asr prayer, including the three qul surahs (Al-Ikhlas, Al-Falaq, An-Nas) which the Prophet prescribed for protection against all forms of harm throughout the night. Each supplication is presented in clear Arabic script alongside its English translation, and the pocket-size format makes this book exceptionally convenient for daily use. The small dimensions allow it to fit easily into a pocket, purse, or bag, ensuring that these essential devotions are always accessible regardless of where the reader happens to be. The book includes references to the source hadith for each supplication, allowing readers to verify the authenticity of the narrations and understand the context in which the Prophet taught them. Additional sections cover supplications for specific situations such as before sleeping, upon entering and leaving the home, before and after eating, and for seeking refuge from various trials. The durable binding and compact construction are designed to withstand daily handling and repeated consultation, making this a reliable companion for the regular practice of prophetic devotions. This edition is particularly suited for new Muslims learning the daily adhkar for the first time, as well as for seasoned practitioners who want a portable reference that keeps these blessed remembrances close at hand throughout the day.`,
