    slug: "punj-surah-with-urdu-translation-4-color",
    description: `Punj Surah with Urdu Translation 4 Color is a beautifully produced edition that presents fifteen selected surahs (chapters) from the Holy Quran alongside their Urdu translation, printed using a distinctive four-colour process that enhances readability and visual appeal. The "Punj Surah" (Five Surahs) tradition in South Asian Islamic culture has been expanded over time, and this edition collects fifteen of the most frequently recited and memorised surahs that every Muslim should know and recite regularly. These include Surah al-Fatihah (the opening chapter recited in every unit of prayer), Surah al-Baqarah's final two verses (Ayat al-Kursi and the concluding verses), Surah Yasin (often called the heart of the Quran), Surah al-Mulk (the chapter that intercedes for its reader), Surah al-Kahf (recommended for recitation every Friday), Surah al-Waqi'ah, Surah al-Rahman, Surah al-Jumu'ah, Surah al-Munafiqun, Surah al-Hashr, Surah al-Saff, Surah al-Jumu'ah, Surah at-Talaq, Surah al-Insan, and Surah al-Mursalat. The four-colour printing process uses distinct colours for the Arabic text, the Urdu translation, the transliteration where included, and the decorative elements, creating a visually rich reading experience that makes it easy to distinguish between the original Quranic text and its translation. The Arabic text is printed in a clear, well-proportioned script with full vowel marks (tashkeel) that aid correct pronunciation and recitation. The Urdu translation is rendered in an accessible and accurate style that conveys the meaning of the Quranic verses without losing the beauty and eloquence of the original Arabic. The page layout is carefully designed to ensure that the Arabic text and its translation appear together on each page, allowing the reader to follow both simultaneously without having to flip back and forth. The physical production quality of this edition is notable, with durable paper, strong binding, and a cover design that reflects the dignity of the Quranic content. This edition is particularly useful for those who are learning to recite the Quran with understanding, for teachers and students in madrasah settings, for families who read these surahs together in their daily devotions, and for anyone who wishes to keep these essential surahs readily accessible in a format that is both beautiful and practical.`,
