    slug: "purani-kitab-qissa-syedna-idrees-silsila-qasas-ul-anbiya-230",
    description: `Purani Kitab (Qissa Syedna Idrees) Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya 2/30 is the second installment in a thirty-part Urdu-language series dedicated to retelling the stories of the Prophets (Qasas ul Anbiya) for younger readers, with this volume focusing specifically on the life and mission of Prophet Idrees (Enoch, peace be upon him). Written by Ishtiaq Ahmed, a well-known author of Islamic children's literature, this book is part of an ambitious project to present the complete narrative of the prophetic tradition in a format that is engaging, educational, and appropriate for young Muslim readers. The title "Purani Kitab" (Ancient Book) evokes the sense of historical depth and sacred heritage that surrounds the stories of the prophets, while the series designation "Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya" (Series of the Stories of the Prophets) places this volume within its broader context as one chapter in a comprehensive retelling of prophetic history. Prophet Idrees holds a special place in Islamic tradition as one of the earliest prophets, mentioned in the Quran alongside Adam and Nuh among those who were granted patience and steadfastness. The book presents the story of Prophet Idrees in a narrative style that brings the ancient world to life, describing the society in which he lived, the challenges he faced in calling his people to the worship of the one true God, and the wisdom and miracles that distinguished his prophethood. Islamic tradition records that Prophet Idrees was the first person to write with a pen, the first to sew garments, and the first to study the science of the stars, making him a figure of great significance in the history of human civilisation and knowledge. The author weaves these traditional details into an engaging story that captures the imagination of young readers while remaining faithful to the authentic Islamic sources. The language is accessible Urdu that children can understand, and the narrative is structured in short chapters that maintain attention and build suspense. Moral lessons are naturally integrated into the story, teaching children about patience, trust in Allah, the importance of knowledge, and the courage to stand for truth even when it is unpopular. This volume, like all books in the series, is produced with attention to quality and durability, featuring clear printing and a format suitable for children's hands. It is an excellent resource for parents who wish to introduce their children to the rich heritage of the prophetic stories in a way that is both enjoyable and spiritually enriching.`,
