    slug: "purani-laash-qissa-syedna-musa-silsila-qasas-ul-anbiya-1530",
    description: `Purani Laash (Qissa Syedna Musa) Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya 15/30 is the fifteenth volume in a comprehensive thirty-part Urdu-language series that narrates the stories of the Prophets, with this particular installment focusing on the remarkable life and mission of Prophet Musa (Moses, peace be upon him). Written by Ishtiaq Ahmed, a respected author in the field of Islamic children's literature, this book addresses the dramatic events surrounding the narrative of the "Purani Laash" (Ancient Remains), which refers to the body that became the subject of dispute among the Children of Israel as mentioned in the Quranic account related to Prophet Musa. The story of Prophet Musa is among the most frequently recounted narratives in the Quran, mentioned in over seventy verses across numerous surahs, making it one of the most detailed prophetic accounts in Islamic scripture. This volume captures the key episodes of Prophet Musa's life, beginning with the perilous circumstances of his birth during the tyrannical reign of Pharaoh, the miraculous preservation of his life through the basket placed on the river, his upbringing in Pharaoh's own palace, his flight to Midian after defending an oppressed man, his marriage and life as a shepherd, the divine encounter at the burning bush where he received his prophetic mission, the spectacular confrontation with Pharaoh's magicians, the parting of the sea, the receiving of the Torah at Mount Sinai, and the long journey of the Children of Israel through the desert. Ishtiaq Ahmed presents these events in a narrative style that is vivid, dramatic, and emotionally engaging, while maintaining strict adherence to the authentic Islamic sources. The Urdu prose is crafted for young readers, using clear language and an exciting pace that keeps children absorbed in the story. Each chapter concludes with reflections on the moral and spiritual lessons embedded in the narrative, helping young readers connect the ancient events to their own lives and faith. The book teaches about the power of faith in the face of seemingly impossible odds, the importance of standing up against injustice, the mercy and power of Allah, and the qualities of true leadership and courage that Prophet Musa exemplified throughout his life. As volume fifteen of thirty, this book fits into the broader educational project of the Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya series, giving children a comprehensive understanding of prophetic history in digestible, age-appropriate installments. This volume is an excellent addition to any child's Islamic library and a valuable teaching resource for parents and educators.`,
